caption.text:
1️⃣ If you average less than 1,000 views per reel 

You need to focus on growing your community. It’s better to use growth CTA, such as: “Follow me for daily Instagram tips” or “Follow me for daily fitness tips,” etc. 

Either as the first line of your caption or at the end of your video.

2️⃣ When you have between 1,000 and 10,000 reel views on average

you can start focusing on inbound lead generation. 

If you are averaging 10,000 views per reel, you can expect up to 1,000 leads per month, with 500 being the minimum. 

It makes sense to include promotional actions in about 30% of your posts. 

For example, you could write in the caption or at the end of your video: «Comment a XYZ keyword to get my [lead magnet]»

3️⃣ If you consistently get over 10,000 reel views per reel, you will have many leads. 

However, especially if you’re selling high-ticket items, not all of them will be qualified leads so it will be a waste of time to message all of them.

Instead, you should ask people to click the link in your bio and fill out a form before getting your lead magnet. 

This allows you to review the forms and pre-qualify leads, so you only need to message those who meet your criteria based on their submissions.

caption.text:
Why post more?

Every IG account has a virality rate.

Let’s say yours is 10%.

This means every 10th reel you post performs better than the others and reaches non-followers.

So, if you post 10 times a month, only one reel reaches non-followers.

But if you post 30 reels a month, you could have 3 viral reels.

As a result, you’ll get more views, more new followers, and more potential clients.

Does this mean that posting more guarantees you’ll get more followers?

Absolutely not!

If you post bad content, your virality rate will be 0%, and you might as well stop posting altogether. 😀

Learn how to create better content first, and only then start scaling your posting.

For example, one of our clients, @aid_anxiety, leveled up her content, started posting twice a day, and grew from 150 followers to 15.4K in 4 months.

Don’t scale bad content. Scale only good content!

And follow me if you want to scale on Instagram. I share daily advanced tips and strategies ✅
